definitions.definition: To move upward , to fly , to soar .
examples: He ascended to heaven upon a cloud.

definitions.definition: To slope in an upward direction.

examples: You ascend the stairs and take a right.

definitions.definition: To succeed a ruler on (the throne).
examples: She ascended the throne when her mother abdicated.
She ascended to the throne when her mother abdicated.

definitions.definition: To rise; to become higher, more noble, etc.
To trace, search or go backwards temporally (e.g., through records, genealogies, routes, etc.).
examples: Our inquiries ascend to the remotest antiquity.

definitions.definition: To cease being an incel , generally by losing one's virginity /having sex , or by forming a romantic relationship .

main_definition: ( intransitive ) To move upward , to fly , to soar .
secondary_definitions: ( intransitive ) To slope in an upward direction.
( ambitransitive ) To succeed a ruler on (the throne).
( intransitive , figurative ) To rise; to become higher, more noble, etc.
To trace, search or go backwards temporally (e.g., through records, genealogies, routes, etc.).
( transitive , music ) To become higher in pitch.
( incel slang ) To cease being an incel , generally by losing one's virginity /having sex , or by forming a romantic relationship .
